title: Cane River National Heritage Area: Reptiles
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Reptiles                Reptiles        Reptiles of Louisiana are plentiful but most are usually not harmful. However some are quite dangerous to both humans and other animals.*Alligators are very dangerous especially during the mating season and when protecting a nest of eggs.Never feed a gator.Some of the most common poisonous snakes include:*rattlesnake*water moccasin or cottonmouth*copperhead or highland moccasin*coral snakeFor more complete information visit   LA Wildlife Web Site:http://www.wlf.state.la.us/ Alligators, Photo by CRNHA
